description:
AntennaUnit: Table containing metadata and attributes for antenna units in a radio access network, including location, identifiers, physical characteristics, and configuration details.

dateTime: Timestamp indicating when the antenna unit data was recorded.
Area_Name: Geographic area where the antenna unit is located.
CellId: Unique identifier for the cell site to which the antenna unit belongs.
Id2: Redundant cell identifier (appears to be the same as CellId).
Id3:  Likely an internal identifier, possibly related to antenna unit grouping.
Id4: Likely an internal identifier, possibly related to antenna unit sub-grouping.
vsDataType: Type of data, indicating that the record refers to an Antenna Unit.
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format used.
AntennaUnit.mechanicalAntennaTilt: Mechanical tilt angle of the antenna (degrees).
AntennaUnit.mechanicalAntennaBearing: Azimuth bearing of the antenna (degrees).  Negative values might indicate missing or invalid data.
AntennaUnit.numberOfLogicalArrays: Number of logical antenna arrays associated with this unit.
AntennaUnit.positionWithinSector: Position or configuration within the sector.  Empty values suggest missing data.
AntennaUnit.sectorLabel: Label or identifier for the sector.  Empty values suggest missing data.
AntennaUnit.antennaUnitId: Unique identifier for the specific antenna unit.
AntennaUnit.antennaModelNumber: Model number of the antenna.
AntennaUnit.antennaSerialNumber: Serial number of the antenna.
AntennaUnit.antennaDataProvenance: Source or origin of the antenna data.  Empty values suggest missing data.
